<span id="freeTextContainer11982398805151531976">Romancing Melody ~ A Crossing Journey~ by Carrie Daws<br/>Romancing Melody the 3rd book in A Crossing Journey series is out of this world. I loved this book and the whole series. Melody and David Podell face a tragedy, military deployment, being away from family and friends all while questioning God. There faith is pushed to the limits. And they need answers to the hard life changing questions, is He trustworthy, how can He love me and allow tragedy. Having faced a similar loss, this book ready hit h</span>
  <span id="freeText11982398805151531976" style="display:none">Romancing Melody ~ A Crossing Journey~ by Carrie Daws<br />Romancing Melody the 3rd book in A Crossing Journey series is out of this world. I loved this book and the whole series. Melody and David Podell face a tragedy, military deployment, being away from family and friends all while questioning God. There faith is pushed to the limits. And they need answers to the hard life changing questions, is He trustworthy, how can He love me and allow tragedy. Having faced a similar loss, this book ready hit home. My heart hurt for the characters. I cried like a baby and still was not able to put this book down. And while it may be fiction it answered question I had and comforted me. Once again Carrie Daws has written a fantastic book that will draw you in and closer to Christ. The characters come alive; you will be grieving, rejoicing and find comfort right along with the resident of Crossing, Oregon. I highly recommend this book. It is an example of true Christian faith and an author that has a strong relationship with our Heavenly Father.</span>
