<div id="review_567975780" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/567975780" />
    <a title="Anne Marie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9201395-anne-marie"><img alt="Anne Marie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1543841087p2/9201395.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/567975780?book_show_action=true">Mar 22, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anne Marie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anne Marie" href="/user/show/9201395-anne-marie">Anne Marie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer567975780" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2175562523708382109">First of all I knew this was going to be another big hit when I read the first paragraph! I loved it from the beginning to the end. We go back to Crossing after Melody and her husband are faced with tragedy and they have to decide if they will trust God during this time in their lives. All the favorite characters from the other books are in this one and they help Melody deal with her pain. This book is one that may make you cry, laugh and just say I can totally relate! Carrie did another AWESOME</span>
  <span id="freeText2175562523708382109" style="display:none">First of all I knew this was going to be another big hit when I read the first paragraph! I loved it from the beginning to the end. We go back to Crossing after Melody and her husband are faced with tragedy and they have to decide if they will trust God during this time in their lives. All the favorite characters from the other books are in this one and they help Melody deal with her pain. This book is one that may make you cry, laugh and just say I can totally relate! Carrie did another AWESOME job on this book and she has become one of my favorite authors! I recommend it to everyone! I don't think you would have to read the other two books first to enjoy this one.<br /><br />*Please note: I received a free copy of this book in exchange for my honest review.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2175562523708382109" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


